    <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Represent a single inline annotation (e.g., bold, italic, link) spanning a character range within document text. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b I/O\/ \:  (int, int, str, str) -&gt; JSON serializable model</para>
<para>The piece of information about the text line: it&apos;s appearance or links to another document object. For example Annotation(1, 13, &quot;italic&quot;, &quot;True&quot;) says that text between 1st and 13th symbol was written in italic.</para>
<para>:ivar start: start of the annotated text :ivar end: end of the annotated text (end isn&apos;t included) :ivar name: annotation&apos;s name, specific for each type of annotation :ivar value: information about annotated text, depends on the type of annotation, e.g. &quot;True&quot;/&quot;False&quot;, &quot;10.0&quot;, etc.</para>
<para>:vartype start: int :vartype end: int :vartype name: str :vartype value: str </para>
    </detaileddescription>
